'''Imperial Saboteurs''' were specially trained soliders skilled in demolitions and [[Saboteur/Legends|sabotage]] in the [[Imperial Remnant]]. Clad in flexible [[Color/Legends|black]] [[Armor/Legends|armor]], they were generally armed with a [[DL-44 heavy blaster pistol/Legends|DL-44 heavy blaster pistol]], an [[E-11 blaster rifle/Legends|E-11 blaster rifle]], or a [[DXR-6 disruptor rifle]]. Additionally, they were equipped with [[Stealth field generator/Legends|stealth field generators]] that rendered them virtually invisible, allowing them to evade enemy defenses.

==History==
Saboteurs operated at various locations throughout the [[Galaxy/Legends|galaxy]] during the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]]. Occasionally, they worked alongside [[Stormtrooper/Legends|stormtroopers]] on [[Planet/Legends|worlds]] of interest to the [[Disciples of Ragnos]], a [[Sith cult/Legends|Sith cult]] backed by the [[Imperial Remnant]].

[[Jaden Korr]], a [[Jedi Knight/Legends|Jedi Knight]] and student of [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker's]] [[Jedi Praxeum]] on [[Yavin 4/Legends|Yavin 4]], encountered several saboteurs during his missions. He foiled several of the saboteurs' plans, including attempts to destroy a [[Bakuran power station|power facility]] on [[Bakura/Legends|Bakura]], and blow up [[Tibanna/Legends|Tibanna]] gas tanks on [[Kril'Dor/Legends|Kril'dor]]. Saboteurs were also employed to deter Korr as he escaped from an Imperial [[Dosuun Imperial facility|facility]] on [[Dosuun]] and hamper his search for [[Rosh Penin]] on [[Taspir III]]. It is not known whether any saboteurs survived the defeat of the Disciples of Ragnos and Imperial Remnant.

